By Obinna Ezugwu Operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has allegedly invaded the Enugu home of Mr. Innocent Chukwuma, CEO of Innoson Vehicle Limited, shooting sporadically into the air and injuring tens of people in the process, the company said through its official facebook page. The action is a fallout of the protracted legal tussle between Guaranty Trust Bank (GTB) and the car manufacturer which has dragged over the years. Meanwhile, the company said Mr. Chukwuma has been arrested and is now being driven to Lagos. Details laterâ€¦